name: politico
text:
From Zoom meetings to mental health check-ins during the work day to reconfiguring office spaces, most defense CEOs say the changes forced by the coronavirus will be permanent even after this crisis is over
https://t.co/MibiUE9mRx

name: politico
text:
As recently as Monday, Trump has tweeted results must be “final” on Nov. 3, which has never been the case for any past election.

In Michigan, Pennsylvania and Wisconsin, officials have warned that results posted on the night of Nov. 3 will be incomplete
https://t.co/Ty63LJTi1D

name: politico
text:
Trump was, however, apparently misreading a Supreme Court ruling on Wisconsin.

SCOTUS declined to reinstate an extension of the ballot return deadline that a lower court ordered. The ruling does not affect when Wisconsin will count the ballots it receives
https://t.co/Ty63LJTi1D

name: politico
text:
Opinion: It was the district court that overstepped its bounds and interfered in Wisconsin’s election, not Kavanaugh, who voted simply to restore the status quo prior to this judicial intervention

https://t.co/bqHNmAUJCC
